GitHub Markdown does **not** support custom font sizes like "5x" directly â€” but it **does support heading levels** (`#` to `######`) to visually enlarge text.

Hereâ€™s how heading sizes appear in GitHub:

| Markdown | Rendered Size Approx. | Usage           |
| -------- | --------------------- | --------------- |
| `#`      | ğŸ”µ 5x (largest)       | Main Title      |
| `##`     | ğŸ”µ 4x                 | Section Heading |
